Title: "GEOMETRIC PROPERTIES" OF SETS OF LINES  
Author: Azriel Rosenfeld 
Address: College Park, MD 20742-3275  
Affiliation: Computer Vision Laboratory Center for Automation Research University of Maryland  
Date: July 1994  
Pubnum: CAR-TR-724  F49620-93-1-0039  
Abstract: When we regard the plane as a set of points, we can define various geometric properties of subsets of the plane|connectedness, convexity, area, diameter, etc. It is well known that the plane can also be regarded as a set of lines. This note considers methods of defining sets (or fuzzy sets) of lines in the plane, and of defining (analogs of) "geometric properties" for The support of the Air Force Office of Scientific Research under Grant F49620-93-1-0039 is gratefully acknowledged, as is the help of Sandy German in preparing this paper. such sets.
